<section xml:id="sec-vectors-in-the-plane" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>Vectors in the plane</title>

  <definition xml:id="def-vector-plane">
    <statement>
      <p>
        A <term>vector</term> in the <m>(x, y)-</m>plane is a directed line segment, which is also called 
        an `arrow'. The set of all vectors in the plane is denoted by <m>\mathbb{R}^2</m>.
      </p>
    </statement>
  </definition>

